oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Spring Hill High School Gym: southeast elevation
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Eatherly, Brad, photographer
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Color photograph of a historic high school gym viewed from the southeast.
The Spring Hill high School Gym was built in 1956 just across the street from the high school. It was named for Maury County school superintendent Rufus Baker.
